@startuml IMEP_Seq_Auth

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #2E86C1
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EBF5FB
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #1A5276
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #5D6D7E
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F8F9FA
skinparam noteBorderColor #F39C12
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEF9E7

title IMEP — Sequence Diagram: Registration, Onboarding & Login

actor        User
participant  "React Frontend"     as FE
participant  "Express API\n/api/auth" as API
participant  "Auth Service"       as SVC
participant  "Token Service"      as TOKEN
database     "MongoDB"            as DB
participant  "Email Service\n(Nodemailer)" as EMAIL

== Registration ==

User -> FE  : Fill form (firstName, lastName,\nemail, password, role)
FE   -> API : POST /api/auth/register\n{ firstName, lastName, email, password, role }
API  -> SVC : register(req, res)
SVC  -> DB  : User.findOne({ email })
DB  --> SVC : null (not found — ok)
SVC  -> SVC : bcrypt.hash(password, 12)
SVC  -> DB  : User.create({ ...userData })
DB  --> SVC : User document saved
SVC  -> TOKEN : generateAccessToken(userId, role)
SVC  -> TOKEN : generateRefreshToken(userId)
TOKEN --> SVC : { accessToken, refreshToken }
SVC  -> DB  : Session.create({ userId, refreshToken, device, ip })
SVC --> API : { user, accessToken }
API --> FE  : 201 { success, data: { user, accessToken } }\nSet-Cookie: refreshToken (httpOnly, secure)
FE   -> FE  : Redux: store accessToken
FE  --> User : Redirect → /onboarding/:role

== Onboarding (Student example) ==

User -> FE  : Fill onboarding form\n(university, department, company,\nwork location, internship dates)
FE   -> API : POST /api/student/onboarding\nAuthorization: Bearer <accessToken>
API  -> API : protect middleware: verify JWT
API  -> API : authorize(['student'])
API  -> DB  : StudentProfile.create({ user, ...profileData })
DB  --> API : Profile saved
API  -> DB  : User.updateOne({ isOnboardingComplete: true })
DB  --> API : Updated
API --> FE  : 200 { success, data: { isOnboardingComplete: true } }
FE   -> FE  : Redux: update auth state
FE  --> User : Redirect → /student/dashboard

== Login ==

User -> FE  : Enter email + password
FE   -> API : POST /api/auth/login\n{ email, password }
API  -> SVC : login(req, res)
SVC  -> DB  : User.findOne({ email }).select('+password')
DB  --> SVC : User document
SVC  -> SVC : user.comparePassword(password)\n(bcrypt.compare)
SVC  -> TOKEN : generateAccessToken(userId, role)
SVC  -> TOKEN : generateRefreshToken(userId)
SVC  -> DB  : Session.findOneAndUpdate (upsert)\n{ device, ip, refreshToken, lastActive }
SVC  -> DB  : User.updateOne({ lastLogin: now })
SVC --> API : { user, accessToken }
API --> FE  : 200 { success, data: { user, accessToken } }\nSet-Cookie: refreshToken (httpOnly, secure)
FE   -> FE  : Redux: store accessToken + user
FE  --> User : Redirect → role dashboard

== Silent Token Refresh ==

note over FE, API : Triggered automatically when API returns 401

FE   -> API : POST /api/auth/refresh\n(Cookie: refreshToken sent automatically)
API  -> TOKEN : verifyRefreshToken(token)
TOKEN -> DB  : Session.findOne({ refreshToken })
DB  --> TOKEN : Session valid
TOKEN -> TOKEN : generateAccessToken(userId, role)
TOKEN --> API : { accessToken }
API --> FE   : 200 { success, data: { accessToken } }
FE   -> FE   : Redux: update accessToken
FE   -> FE   : Retry original failed request

@enduml
